<br>
When I hit my assist hotkey, and have my pet attack whatever we're fighting, if there are 2 monsters with the same name it will go for one of them, but not necessarily the one everyone else (including me) has targetted. So, my question is, how do you handle this when you are grouped with an enchanter who is mezzing? (Or, am I doing something wrong and should be able to get my pet to go after, say, the one gobby warlord (out of 4) that everyone else it fighting..?)<br>
<br>
If that's the case, how do I do that then?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for any help you can give me! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxushni.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xushni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/02 8:40:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.animationfactory.com/animations/people_m_z/wizard/wizard_raisehands_md_clr.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: grouping question (I think it would go here...)</span><hr size=1> I shouldn't be going after one different than the person you are assisting, even if they have the same name. If that is really the case, then /bug iand report that.<br>
<br>
Make sure your hot key says<br>
<br>
/assist soandso<br>
<br>
soandso being your main tanks name of course.<br>
<br>
Hit it a couple(maybe more)times, and when you can be sure he is on the target he wants(cuz know sometimes a warrior gets multiples, but may switch to different target for one reason or the other, its the highest level, its a cleric, etc)<br>
<br>
Then /pet attack hotkey. Should work fine, if it attacks somethign else then it might have gotten hit by that mob while running towards its target, but I have never had this happen to me personally so no definate suggestions <p><img src=http://photos.netclubs.com/live/photos/photocenter/9/a/g/e/ge31rtf4brah3bpd0188nc11hc/sig.JPG></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uapprenhightowerr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Appren Hightowerr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#333333>(3/3/02 2:51:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: grouping question (I think it would go here...)</span><hr size=1> Aye, good advice from Xushi, when I am in a group myself, I use 2 assist keys, one that is /assist maintankname and one that is just /assist.<br>
<br>
Also even if you assist the main tank, mob number 2 might take a swing at your pet, so I suggest you dont send pet in before the extra mobs(s) are mezzed, and then be sure tank havent switched target. <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=99814
