</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uteamnoir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>teamnoir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(3/8/02 6:54:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: grouping question (I think it would go here...)</span><hr size=1> Another thing I noticed recently as beastlord... pet seems to work on a hate list.  So even if other mobs are mezzed when pet goes in, one of them is likely to break mez and score pet hate before being remezzed.  In which case, as soon as mob #1 dies, pet will break mez on the other.<br>
<br>
To fix this, when working in a group with a chanter, use /pet back off, which clears pet's hate list.  Do this just before the mob he's on dies.  Let someone else score the killing blow.<br>
<br>
Another possibility, and one we've used some, is to let pet pick the targets.  Have everyone else assist pet.  While this seems to work at lower levels, I think it would get to be a problem in the upper levels when chanter sieves and pays attention to which mobs will break mez next.  In that case, you really want chanter to point out the next mob, I think.<br>
<br>
Aanni - mage20<br>
Auji - beastlady33<br>
Aidal - cleric 54<br>
and a cast of many others <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ankha>Ankha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(3/13/02 4:47:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: grouping question (I think it would go here...)</span><hr size=1> Thanks for those tips. I'm now level 27, and have only had one<br>
bad incident in a group. We had the one pull, and 3 adds. I took my time before sending the pet in (we did have an enchanter) and was very glad I'd read those suggestions - the warrior changed his mind 5 times before he finally decided on which one to attack!<br>
<br>
Thanks again!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unightfog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nightfog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#333333>(3/13/02 5:32:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.familjenguild.com/new/members/images/thumb_amel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: grouping question (I think it would go here...)</span><hr size=1> I actually have two hotkeys as someone above mentioned.<br>
<br>
One is /target MainTanksName (This is so I can damageshield him)<br>
Then /assist withouta name.<br>
<br>
That way I have my Main tank targeted.  then when he calls to assist I /assist.  and send in my pet.  <br>
<br>
Then as the battles continue I /assist the monster to see who's he's attacking so I can damage shield anyone that may be drawing his agro.<br>
<br>
Just a tip.<br>
<br>
Also when sending in the pets.  It's a good idea to wait till the mobs are on the main tank or mezzed before you send in your pet.  you're not going to lose that much damage by waiting 5 seconds to send in a pet.<br>
<br>
<br>
Oh and another tip.  If there are adds I will /pet back off before the mob dies just to make sure that my pets agro is clear before the mob dies.  If the mob dies and another mob got on your pets hate list he'll charge after the next mob breaking the mez early.  This will often piss off your group :&quot; )<br>
