<img src=http://network54.com/Realm/foggybottom/pic/AmelFamiljen.JPG></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unightfog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nightfog</A> at: 3/13/02 5:35:20 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uommundan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ommundan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.datecc.de/bilder/woag/bilder/misc/misc59d.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#333333>(3/14/02 4:19:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.cfl.rr.com/exarch/files/PAINT1.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: grouping question (I think it would go here...)</span><hr size=1> Great tip on /assisting the monster and DS'ing his target. I do that anytime I am passing through areas and want to help the groups out with damage shields <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Another way to save a hotkey slot is that when you're in a group you can use the F2, F3, F4, F5, F6 keys to target party members.<br>
<br>
Also, when you make an assist key, set it up like this:<br>
<br>
..blank line..<br>
..blank line..<br>
/assist<br>
<br>
then when you go into a group you can modify it to this:<br>
<br>
/target tank<br>
/target tank<br>
/assist<br>
<br>
or just modify it to read:<br>
<br>
/assist tank<br>
<br>
I still take on many multi mob camps so I need a blank assist so that I can target whatever my pet is beating on.<br>
<br>
The blank /assist key is also good for switching back and forth from the mob to yor pet in close fights or when chain casting so that you know when to nuke/heal/summon a new pet.<br>
<br>
Great stuff here, keep em coming <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Good hunting,<br>
